redpanda's compose uses `depends_on: { broker: { condition: service_healthy }}`, but nerdctl-in-VM ignores healthcheck blocks — broker has no healthcheck registered, so docker compose v2 refuses to satisfy `service_healthy` for the probe service ("container has no healthcheck configured"). Until nerdctl honors compose healthchecks, this scenario can't run via docker compose against gocker.sock. Works fine through `gocker compose` because our compose proxy uses external poll-based readiness.
